The paper deals with deep-learning-based image colorization, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of adversarial methods (cs.LG) and meta-learning techniques (cs.AI) to enhance the generator model. Additionally, the paper involves the use of clustering techniques (cs.MM) to divide the training dataset into task-oriented clusters. Finally, the paper discusses the results and future developments of the proposed method, which could be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) research.
